{"parentUuid":"dec58a21-0d35-464e-af12-2936d2de43b8","isSidechain":false,"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Trellis Launch\n\nArguments:  (optional path to a plan.md)\n\nGreenfield build. You're starting from a plan and need to build a working app.\nThis is the Launch phase — the one-time path from plan → working code. After\ncompletion the project transitions to Refine.\n\n**For v2.0-alpha**: Launch runs the existing P1-P6 pipeline internally. The user\nsees `LAUNCH` in the statusline; the internal stages (decompose → contracts →\nskeleton → build → assemble → polish) are implementation detail. Consolidation\nto 3 internal stages (Plan / Build / Polish) is deferred to v2.0-beta.\n\n## 0. Bootstrap infrastructure\n\nEnsure `.framework/`, hooks, and `settings.json` are installed. `init.sh` is\nidempotent — safe to run every time.\n\n```bash\nbash ~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/init.sh .\n```\n\nThis creates (or updates) `.framework/`, `.framework/flags/`, copies hooks into\n`.claude/hooks/`, and patches `settings.json` to register the v2 hook set.\n\nPhase instruction files and contract templates are NOT copied into the project.\nThey live in the global install at `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/framework/` and\n`~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/templates/`. The steps below reference them from\nthere.\n\n## 1. Gate: don't overwrite existing work\n\nIf `.framework/state.json` exists and `phase` is `refine`, STOP. Re-running Launch\nover a project that's already in Refine would wipe the app-map and features and\ndestroy in-progress work. Tell the user to use `/trellis-feature` instead, or run\n`/trellis-upgrade` if they genuinely want to rebuild from scratch (rare).\n\n```bash\nif [ -f .framework/state.json ]; then\n  CURRENT_PHASE=$(python3 -c \"import json; print(json.load(open('.framework/state.json')).get('phase',''))\")\n  if [ \"$CURRENT_PHASE\" = \"refine\" ]; then\n    echo \"Project is in Refine. Launch would clobber existing work. Stop and ask user.\"\n    exit 1\n  fi\nfi\n```\n\n## 2. Initialize state\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p .framework/flags\nPLAN_PATH=\"${ARGUMENTS:-.framework/plan.md}\"\npython3 ~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/state.py init . --origin greenfield\npython3 ~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/state.py command . /trellis-launch\n```\n\nIf `` was a path to a plan file, copy it into `.framework/plan.md`:\n```bash\nif [ -n \"\" ] && [ -f \"\" ] && [ \"\" != \".framework/plan.md\" ]; then\n  cp \"\" .framework/plan.md\nfi\n```\n\n## 3. Run the build pipeline\n\nFollow the phase instruction files in the global install at\n`~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/framework/`:\n\n1. **Phase 1: Decompose** — `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/framework/phase1-decomposition.md`\n   Break the plan into components per layer (data/ui/logic/theme).\n2. **Phase 2: Contracts** — `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/framework/phase2-contracts.md`\n   Generate typed contracts per component. User review gate.\n3. **Phase 3: Skeleton** — `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/framework/phase3-skeleton.md`\n   Create scaffolding + stubs. Run codegen.\n4. **Phase 4: Parallel Build** — `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/framework/phase4-parallel-build.md`\n   Sonnet agents fill stubs in parallel, one per layer group.\n5. **Phase 5: Assembly** — `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/framework/phase5-assembly.md`\n   Wire components into screens following the assembly manifest.\n6. **Phase 6: Polish** — `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/framework/phase6-polish.md`\n   Integration tests, smoke tests, walkthrough.\n\nContract templates (for Phase 2) live at `~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/templates/`.\n\nBetween phases, update `progress.md` to reflect the current internal stage.\nThe top-level statusline phase stays `LAUNCH` throughout — internal stages are\nnot promoted to the top-level phase.\n\n## 4. After polish — transition to Refine\n\nOnce Phase 6 is complete and the user has walked through the app:\n\n```bash\n# Generate the app-map (Flutter-aware if applicable)\nif [ -f pubspec.yaml ]; then\n  python3 ~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/generate-app-map.py .\nelse\n  python3 ~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/generate-app-map-generic.py .\nfi\n\n# Transition\npython3 ~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/state.py phase . refine\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat: initial build complete (launch → refine)\"\n```\n\nAsk the user to confirm before the transition — same approval pattern as mode\nclosure. Launch → Refine is a one-way door; they should see what's in the app-map\nbefore committing to Refine.\n\n## 5. Report\n\nTell the user:\n- What was built (screens, components, count of files)\n- Test status (passing/failing counts)\n- Any known gaps or deferrals\n- Next step: \"Start a refinement with `/trellis-fix`, `/trellis-feature`, or `/trellis-enhance`.\"\n"}]},"isMeta":true,"uuid":"9b5dc61c-8669-4d41-a809-9803d1ecc2bc","timestamp":"2026-04-19T17:20:34.282Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.114","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
{"parentUuid":"9b5dc61c-8669-4d41-a809-9803d1ecc2bc","isSidechain":false,"attachment":{"type":"deferred_tools_delta","addedNames":["AskUserQuestion","CronCreate","CronDelete","CronList","EnterPlanMode","EnterWorktree","ExitPlanMode","ExitWorktree","LSP","Monitor","NotebookEdit","PushNotification","RemoteTrigger","TaskCreate","TaskGet","TaskList","TaskOutput","TaskStop","TaskUpdate","WebFetch","WebSearch","mcp__claude_ai_Gmail__authenticate","mcp__claude_ai_Gmail__complete_authentication","mcp__claude_ai_Google_Calendar__authenticate","mcp__claude_ai_Google_Calendar__complete_authentication","mcp__claude_ai_Google_Drive__authenticate","mcp__claude_ai_Google_Drive__complete_authentication"],"addedLines":["AskUserQuestion","CronCreate","CronDelete","CronList","EnterPlanMode","EnterWorktree","ExitPlanMode","ExitWorktree","LSP","Monitor","NotebookEdit","PushNotification","RemoteTrigger","TaskCreate","TaskGet","TaskList","TaskOutput","TaskStop","TaskUpdate","WebFetch","WebSearch","mcp__claude_ai_Gmail__authenticate","mcp__claude_ai_Gmail__complete_authentication","mcp__claude_ai_Google_Calendar__authenticate","mcp__claude_ai_Google_Calendar__complete_authentication","mcp__claude_ai_Google_Drive__authenticate","mcp__claude_ai_Google_Drive__complete_authentication"],"removedNames":[]},"type":"attachment","uuid":"4197e7f8-1073-4703-9a1a-51283fd7f065","timestamp":"2026-04-19T17:20:34.282Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.114","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
{"parentUuid":"4197e7f8-1073-4703-9a1a-51283fd7f065","isSidechain":false,"attachment":{"type":"skill_listing","content":"- update-config: Use this skill to configure the Claude Code harness via settings.json. Automated behaviors (\"from now on when X\", \"each time X\", \"whenever X\", \"before/after X\") require hooks configured in settings.json - the harness executes these, not Claude, so memory/preferences cannot fulfill them. Also use for: permissions (\"allow X\", \"add permission\", \"move permission to\"), env vars (\"set X=Y\"), hook troubleshooting, or any changes to settings.json/settings.local.json files. Examples: \"allow npm commands\", \"add bq permission to global settings\", \"move permission to user settings\", \"set DEBUG=true\", \"when claude stops show X\". For simple settings like theme/model, use Config tool.\n- keybindings-help: Use when the user wants to customize keyboard shortcuts, rebind keys, add chord bindings, or modify ~/.claude/keybindings.json. Examples: \"rebind ctrl+s\", \"add a chord shortcut\", \"change the submit key\", \"customize keybindings\".\n- simplify: Review changed code for reuse, quality, and efficiency, then fix any issues found.\n- fewer-permission-prompts: Scan your transcripts for common read-only Bash and MCP tool calls, then add a prioritized allowlist to project .claude/settings.json to reduce permission prompts.\n- loop: Run a prompt or slash command on a recurring interval (e.g. /loop 5m /foo). Omit the interval to let the model self-pace. - When the user wants to set up a recurring task, poll for status, or run something repeatedly on an interval (e.g. \"check the deploy every 5 minutes\", \"keep running /babysit-prs\"). Do NOT invoke for one-off tasks.\n- schedule: Create, update, list, or run scheduled remote agents (triggers) that execute on a cron schedule. - When the user wants to schedule a recurring remote agent, set up automated tasks, create a cron job for Claude Code, or manage their scheduled agents/triggers.\n- claude-api: Build, debug, and optimize Claude API / Anthropic SDK apps. Apps built with this skill should include prompt caching. Also handles migrating existing Claude API code between Claude model versions (4.5 → 4.6, 4.6 → 4.7, retired-model replacements).\nTRIGGER when: code imports `anthropic`/`@anthropic-ai/sdk`; user asks for the Claude API, Anthropic SDK, or Managed Agents; user adds/modifies/tunes a Claude feature (caching, thinking, compaction, tool use, batch, files, citations, memory) or model (Opus/Sonnet/Haiku) in a file; questions about prompt caching / cache hit rate in an Anthropic SDK project.\nSKIP: file imports `openai`/other-provider SDK, filename like `*-openai.py`/`*-generic.py`, provider-neutral code, general programming/ML.\n- trellis-update: Update Framework Files\n- trellis-map: Trellis Map\n- trellis-init: Initialize Trellis\n- trellis-discover: Trellis Discover\n- trellis-fix: Trellis Fix\n- viz: Claude Code Viz\n- trellis-launch: Trellis Launch\n- trellis-upgrade: Trellis Upgrade\n- trellis-memory-init: Trellis Memory Init\n- trellis-feature: Trellis Feature\n- trellis-save: Trellis Save\n- trellis-enhance: Trellis Enhance\n- init: Initialize a new CLAUDE.md file with codebase documentation\n- review: Review a pull request\n- security-review: Complete a security review of the pending changes on the current branch","skillCount":22,"isInitial":true},"type":"attachment","uuid":"e87ad3f2-4fe4-4bfb-886c-8b2aa85e5fa9","timestamp":"2026-04-19T17:20:34.282Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.114","gitBranch":"HEAD"}
