{"parentUuid":"f48c5985-8037-4af3-b24d-7871cdcee56d","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01XimTHm4qizjeGnRdGJFhBy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HC3Y8kKVDufFyEiJ6AUYaP","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"cat ~/.claude/frameworks/trellis/framework/phase1-decomposition.md 2>&1","description":"Read Phase 1 decomposition instructions"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24866,"cache_read_input_tokens":14816,"output_tokens":1073,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":24866,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":6,"output_tokens":1073,"cache_read_input_tokens":14816,"cache_creation_input_tokens":24866,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":24866},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"previous_message_not_found"}}},"requestId":"req_011CadCQDf5sYKrTAfLTCewS","type":"assistant","uuid":"5c5b627f-1d4a-41b5-82ab-787087fb87b0","timestamp":"2026-05-02T05:34:18.385Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"5c5b627f-1d4a-41b5-82ab-787087fb87b0","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"616ce004-0002-46e0-8563-f4bf7e0b4a9f","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HC3Y8kKVDufFyEiJ6AUYaP","type":"tool_result","content":"# Phase 1: Decomposition\n\n**Goal**: Facilitate a freeform discussion with the user about what they want to build, then extract and structure everything into `.framework/plan.md`.\n\n## Process\n\n### Step 1: Freeform Discussion\n\nLet the user describe their vision however they want. Listen, then ask follow-up questions to fill gaps. Do NOT present a template upfront — let the conversation flow naturally.\n\n**Key areas to cover** (ask about these if the user hasn't mentioned them):\n\n- What does the app do? Who is it for?\n- What platform? (web, mobile, desktop, CLI)\n- Walk me through the main screens / pages / views\n- What data does the app persist? Where?\n- What are the main user interactions on each screen?\n- Are there shared visual patterns across screens? (lists, cards, forms, avatars, etc.)\n- What's the most complex interaction or feature?\n- Any specific tech stack preferences?\n- Any non-functional requirements? (offline support, performance, accessibility)\n\n### Step 2: Decompose into Components\n\nOnce you have a clear picture, decompose the application into components following these rules:\n\n1. **Single responsibility** — if you can't describe a component in one sentence, split it\n2. **Interface over implementation** — define inputs/outputs, not internals\n3. **Layer 1 (Data) and Layer 2 (UI) have zero cross-dependencies**\n4. **Layer 3 (Logic) depends on Layer 1 only**\n5. **Identify shared components** — if two screens need the same visual pattern, it's one UI atom used twice\n\n**Layer definitions:**\n\n- **Layer 1: Data** — Storage, persistence, external data access. Each owns: schema + DAO + model + state provider.\n- **Layer 2: UI Atoms** — Self-contained visual building blocks. Props in, callbacks out. Know nothing about app context.\n- **Layer 3: Logic** — Business logic, state machines, services. Pure logic, no UI. Depends on L1.\n- **Layer 4: Theme** — Colors, typography, spacing, design tokens.\n\n### Step 3: Define Build Tiers\n\nAssign components to agents for parallel build:\n\n- **Tier 1** (max parallelism): All L1 + L2 + L4 components. Assign to 2-4 agents by layer.\n- **Tier 2**: All L3 components. Assign to 1-2 agents.\n- **Tier 3**: Assembly (single agent).\n\nKeep agent count between 2-6 total. Each agent builds multiple components sequentially within their layer.\n\n### Step 4: Produce `plan.md`\n\nRead `.framework/templates/plan-structure.md` for the required structure. Fill in every section based on the discussion. All YAML blocks must be complete — these are machine-extracted in Phase 2.\n\nPresent `.framework/plan.md` to the user for review. Iterate until approved.\n\n### Step 5: Create `progress.md`\n\nAfter user approves `.framework/plan.md`, create `.framework/progress.md`:\n\n```markdown\n# Project Progress\n\n## Current Phase\nphase: 1\nstatus: complete\nnext_action: Generate interface contracts (Phase 2)\n\n## Phase History\n- phase: 1, completed: {date}, output: .framework/plan.md\n\n## Session Handoff\nlast_session: {date}\nlast_action: Phase 1 complete\nnext_steps:\n  - Generate interface contracts (Phase 2)\npending_issues: []\n\n## Components\n\n| Component | Layer | Contract | Built | Tests | Merged |\n|-----------|-------|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n{one row per component from .framework/plan.md, all columns after Layer set to \"-\"}\n\n## Assembly\n\n| Screen | Slots | Wired | Tests | Status |\n|--------|-------|-------|-------|--------|\n{one row per screen from .framework/plan.md, all set to \"pending\"}\n```\n\n**Always update the Session Handoff section** when starting/completing a phase or when a session ends. See CLAUDE.md for the full schema and resume instructions.\n\n## Completion Gate\n\n- [ ] `.framework/plan.md` exists with all sections filled and YAML blocks complete\n- [ ] User has reviewed and approved `.framework/plan.md`\n- [ ] `.framework/progress.md` exists and shows Phase 1 complete\n- [ ] Component count is reasonable (not over-decomposed — inline anything with 1-2 props used once)","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"2352e192-f3ee-45d6-9132-1a5950db476c","timestamp":"2026-05-02T05:36:01.874Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"# Phase 1: Decomposition\n\n**Goal**: Facilitate a freeform discussion with the user about what they want to build, then extract and structure everything into `.framework/plan.md`.\n\n## Process\n\n### Step 1: Freeform Discussion\n\nLet the user describe their vision however they want. Listen, then ask follow-up questions to fill gaps. Do NOT present a template upfront — let the conversation flow naturally.\n\n**Key areas to cover** (ask about these if the user hasn't mentioned them):\n\n- What does the app do? Who is it for?\n- What platform? (web, mobile, desktop, CLI)\n- Walk me through the main screens / pages / views\n- What data does the app persist? Where?\n- What are the main user interactions on each screen?\n- Are there shared visual patterns across screens? (lists, cards, forms, avatars, etc.)\n- What's the most complex interaction or feature?\n- Any specific tech stack preferences?\n- Any non-functional requirements? (offline support, performance, accessibility)\n\n### Step 2: Decompose into Components\n\nOnce you have a clear picture, decompose the application into components following these rules:\n\n1. **Single responsibility** — if you can't describe a component in one sentence, split it\n2. **Interface over implementation** — define inputs/outputs, not internals\n3. **Layer 1 (Data) and Layer 2 (UI) have zero cross-dependencies**\n4. **Layer 3 (Logic) depends on Layer 1 only**\n5. **Identify shared components** — if two screens need the same visual pattern, it's one UI atom used twice\n\n**Layer definitions:**\n\n- **Layer 1: Data** — Storage, persistence, external data access. Each owns: schema + DAO + model + state provider.\n- **Layer 2: UI Atoms** — Self-contained visual building blocks. Props in, callbacks out. Know nothing about app context.\n- **Layer 3: Logic** — Business logic, state machines, services. Pure logic, no UI. Depends on L1.\n- **Layer 4: Theme** — Colors, typography, spacing, design tokens.\n\n### Step 3: Define Build Tiers\n\nAssign components to agents for parallel build:\n\n- **Tier 1** (max parallelism): All L1 + L2 + L4 components. Assign to 2-4 agents by layer.\n- **Tier 2**: All L3 components. Assign to 1-2 agents.\n- **Tier 3**: Assembly (single agent).\n\nKeep agent count between 2-6 total. Each agent builds multiple components sequentially within their layer.\n\n### Step 4: Produce `plan.md`\n\nRead `.framework/templates/plan-structure.md` for the required structure. Fill in every section based on the discussion. All YAML blocks must be complete — these are machine-extracted in Phase 2.\n\nPresent `.framework/plan.md` to the user for review. Iterate until approved.\n\n### Step 5: Create `progress.md`\n\nAfter user approves `.framework/plan.md`, create `.framework/progress.md`:\n\n```markdown\n# Project Progress\n\n## Current Phase\nphase: 1\nstatus: complete\nnext_action: Generate interface contracts (Phase 2)\n\n## Phase History\n- phase: 1, completed: {date}, output: .framework/plan.md\n\n## Session Handoff\nlast_session: {date}\nlast_action: Phase 1 complete\nnext_steps:\n  - Generate interface contracts (Phase 2)\npending_issues: []\n\n## Components\n\n| Component | Layer | Contract | Built | Tests | Merged |\n|-----------|-------|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n{one row per component from .framework/plan.md, all columns after Layer set to \"-\"}\n\n## Assembly\n\n| Screen | Slots | Wired | Tests | Status |\n|--------|-------|-------|-------|--------|\n{one row per screen from .framework/plan.md, all set to \"pending\"}\n```\n\n**Always update the Session Handoff section** when starting/completing a phase or when a session ends. See CLAUDE.md for the full schema and resume instructions.\n\n## Completion Gate\n\n- [ ] `.framework/plan.md` exists with all sections filled and YAML blocks complete\n- [ ] User has reviewed and approved `.framework/plan.md`\n- [ ] `.framework/progress.md` exists and shows Phase 1 complete\n- [ ] Component count is reasonable (not over-decomposed — inline anything with 1-2 props used once)","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"5c5b627f-1d4a-41b5-82ab-787087fb87b0","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/avinkrism4pro/Personal/apps/MyApps/whatAmIDoing","sessionId":"72a03414-ba52-4106-b27a-7f28ae50fe45","version":"2.1.126","gitBranch":"main"}
